<p>This course raises awareness of your own mental health. It provides tools that improve wellbeing, and it encourages you to talk about your mental health and ask for help when you need it. This course is fully approved by the Institution of Occupational Safety and Health (IOSH). It is also CPD approved.</p>

<p>It is made up of 4 learning areas:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Mental health awareness</li>
    <li>Mental health problems</li>
    <li>Your wellbeing toolkit</li>
    <li>External help and further guidance</li>
</ol>

<p>It will take approximately 40 minutes to complete, with a short quiz at the end.</p>

<h2>To do the course:</h2>

<ol>
    <li>Visit the <a href="https://app.ihasco.co.uk/d01y17">IHASCO website</a> and use your Suffolk Libraries email address to log in.</li>

<img src="/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ihasco-login.jpg" alt="The login page on the IHASCO website">

    <li>Fill in your details and preferences on the form that appears and press 'Create account'</li>
    <li>Click on the 'Mental Health Awareness' course on the 'My learning' screen that appears.</li>

<img src="/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/my-learning.jpg" alt="The My learning page on the IHASCO website">

    <li>Click on the green 'Start Session' button in the right hand corner to start the course. You can come back and resume the course whenever you like.</li>

<img src="/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/start-session-2.jpg" alt="The Mental Health Awareness course page on the IHASCO website">

<li>When you've completed the course, <a href="https://slintranet.co.uk/lessons/complete-the-mental-health-awareness-course-on-ihasco/">mark the course complete here on the intranet</a>. You can also print off a certificate from IHASCO if you like!</li>
